\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Illustration of how agent skills are used in a software engineering workflow. Given a natural-language requirement, the LLM-based agent selects the most relevant skill from its skill library, including skills such as writing code, running tests, debugging, creating pull requests, and deploying, and injects it into the context window. The agent then executes a series of SWE actions to produce the final software artifacts (such as code) that fulfill the requirement.}}{2}{figure.caption.2}\protected@file@percent }
